 Two new core investors have acquired major equity stakes of about 44.3 per cent in Mutual Benefits Assurance Plc in primary deals valued at about N4.8 billion. Mutual Benefits Assurance had through a private placement sold 8.889 billion ordinary shares of 50 kobo each at 54 kobo per share to Charles Enterprise LL.C and Arubiewe Farms Limited. The insurance company formally concluded the transactions yesterday with the listing of the 8.889 billion ordinary shares allocated to the two firms on the Nigerian Exchange (NGX) Limited. With the listing of the additional 8.889 billion ordinary shares, the total issued and fully paid up shares of Mutual Benefits Assurance Plc increased from 11.172 billion to 20.062 billion ordinary shares of 50 kobo each.